No, they won't count towards the major, but you can get units from the Data Science department
Can becoming a Reader/Tutor/TA be counted as EECS technical units?

history.content:
APPLY to be a (U)GSI, Group Tutor or Reader for a DATA course in Spring 2021: Data C8, C100/200, C140 (a.k.a. Stat 140 or Prob 140) or C102.

**Please remember that you must fill out the main form linked above AND the CDSS Supplemental info form linked at the bottom of the main form.**

The priority deadline is October 30.

While applications may be submitted after October 30, your best chance of being considered is to submit BOTH application forms by the priority deadline.
history.subject: DATA Course Staff Application Deadline: OCTOBER 30
